about.description:
SciPy is a Python-based ecosystem of open-source software for mathematics,
science, and engineering.

name: scipy
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.5.2" %}
{% set ver_major_minor = ".".join(version.split(".")[:2]) %}

package:
  name: scipy
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/scipy/scipy/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f2c055e286a9421135407d3cb3efd3f1f7ae9a465b5edc0be14ac8c5c63f6ea1

build:
  number: 2
  skip: true  # [win or py2k]

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - pybind11                               # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - libblas
    - libcblas
    - liblapack
    - python
    - setuptools
    - cython
    - pybind11
    - numpy
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  requires:
    - pytest
    - pytest-xdist
    - mpmath
{% if ver_major_minor == "1.5" %}
    - blas * netlib  # [ppc64le]
{% endif %}

about:
  home: http://www.scipy.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Scientific Library for Python
  description: |
    SciPy is a Python-based ecosystem of open-source software for mathematics,
    science, and engineering.
  doc_url: http://www.scipy.org/docs.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/scipy/scipy

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jakirkham
    - msarahan
    - rgommers
    - ocefpaf
    - beckermr
